maml:description.maml:para: Creates new appointments.

maml:alert.maml:para: You need to add proper permission to the default Calendar folder for each mailbox user.
The appointment is created and saved to the default Calendar folder. You cannot change it.
The default value of StartDate, EndDate and RecurrenceRangeStart is generated automatically in the same manner as what you see in Outlook Web App.
It's recommended to use Show-Command cmdlet that is available in Windows PowerShell V3 to understand the different parameters and parameter sets of New-OSCEXOAppointment

dev:remarks.maml:para: Creates an appointment in the default Calendar for mailbox user John Doe (johnd).
Creates an appointment in the default Calendar for mailbox user John Doe (johnd) by using impersonation.
Creates an all-day event in the default Calendar folder for the mailbox users John Doe (johnd) and Jane Doe (janed).
Creates a recurrence appointment in the default Calendar for mailbox user John Doe (johnd).
